<HelpLayout title="Syncing Your Data" category="Mobile Apps" description="How cloud sync works across devices and what happens when you're offline.">
  <p>
    Plantgotchi uses an offline-first architecture. Your phone is the primary data store, and
    the cloud is a sync layer that keeps everything accessible across devices.
  </p>

  <h2>How Sync Works</h2>
  <p>
    When your device is online, the app syncs with Turso — a distributed SQLite database in
    the cloud. Sync happens in two directions:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Push</strong> — sensor readings and care logs are uploaded from your phone to the cloud.</li>
    <li><strong>Pull</strong> — plant profiles and AI recommendations are downloaded to your phone.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The sync protocol uses Turso's HTTP pipeline API, batching multiple SQL statements into a
    single request for efficiency.
  </p>

  <h2>Conflict Resolution</h2>
  <p>
    What happens when two phones record data for the same plant? Plantgotchi handles this gracefully:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Sensor readings</strong> — deduplicated by a unique constraint on <code>(sensor_id, timestamp)</code>. If two phones capture the same BLE reading, <code>INSERT OR IGNORE</code> keeps just one copy.</li>
    <li><strong>Care logs</strong> — each log has a UUID, so entries from different phones are both preserved (no conflict).</li>
    <li><strong>Plant edits</strong> — last push wins. If you rename a plant on two devices, the most recently synced name is kept.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Offline Mode</h2>
  <p>
    When you're offline, the app works normally:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>BLE sensor readings continue to be captured and stored locally.</li>
    <li>The offline rule engine still generates alerts instantly.</li>
    <li>Care actions are logged to the local database.</li>
    <li>All pending changes are queued and automatically synced when connectivity returns.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The only features that require internet are AI recommendations (from Claude) and accessing
    your garden from the web dashboard.
  </p>

  <h2>Sync Frequency</h2>
  <p>
    The app syncs automatically when it detects a network connection. You can also trigger a
    manual sync by pulling down on the garden screen. AI recommendations run on a 6-hour cycle
    when online.
  </p>
</HelpLayout>
